    "updated_at": "2024-10-26T12:19:31Z",
    "body": "The status argument given to the transient prompt function has an unexpected value, it seems to use the the exit code of the _previous_ command instead of the command that is printed on the current line:\r\n\r\n![image](https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/60f6d30d-a47f-476d-a7f5-a29513ce3163)\r\n\r\nFor example, the `ERROR` printed for the `exit 64` line reflects the exit code of the `exit 1` command. I would expect it to be printed on the corresponding command's line, not after it.\r\n\r\n\r\n<details>\r\n<summary><code>starship_transient_prompt_func</code> definition</summary>\r\n\r\n```fish\r\nfunction starship_transient_prompt_func\r\n    echo \"$(starship module custom.horizontal_line)\"\r\n\r\n    # Parse the status argument\r\n    argparse --ignore-unknown status= -- $argv\r\n    if set --query _flag_status\r\n        set prompt_status \" $(starship module status --status $_flag_status)\"\r\n    else\r\n        set prompt_status \"\"\r\n    end\r\n    echo \"$(starship module time)$prompt_status \"\r\nend\r\n```\r\n\r\n</details>\r\n\r\n",
